1.00	Thomas_J._Samuelian	Thomas J. Samuelian	Thomas J. Samuelian is an American author of a number of books and articles in the field of Armenian language, literature, and history. He has taught at the University of Pennsylvania, Columbia University, and St. Nersess Seminary. He has a Ph.D. in linguistics from the University of Pennsylvania. Dean of the Law faculty, American University of Armenia. He is Chairman of the Board of the Arak-29 Foundation.	
